20. Marine Protected Area Coordinator
Sulu Sea Conservation Alliance
üìç Puerto Princesa City, Palawan, Philippines
The Sulu Sea Conservation Alliance is a regional NGO working to protect critical marine biodiversity across the Sulu-Sulawesi Marine Ecoregion. We support the establishment and management of marine protected areas (MPAs), promote sustainable fisheries, and engage coastal communities in marine conservation. Our work spans the Philippines, Malaysia, and Indonesia.
INTERNSHIP OPPORTUNITY:
6-month paid internship (with potential for full-time employment) supporting MPA coordination activities in Palawan.
What you'll do:

Assist in monitoring fish populations and coral reef health within MPAs through underwater surveys
Support community-based MPA management committees with administrative and technical tasks
Help organize coastal cleanups, information campaigns, and community events
Collect data on fishing activities and MPA compliance
Prepare monitoring reports and maintain project databases
Participate in enforcement patrols with municipal fish wardens

Who should apply:

Recent graduate or final-year student in Marine Biology, Environmental Science, or Fisheries
SCUBA certified (Open Water minimum; Advanced preferred)
Strong interest in marine conservation and community-based resource management
Good interpersonal skills and ability to work with diverse communities
Filipino citizenship required
Fluent in English and Filipino; Cuyonon or other local languages a plus

Type: Internship (6 months, full-time, with stipend)
Deadline: November 20, 2025